To run this app:
1. Make sure you have a .env file with SLACK_BOT_TOKEN, SLACK_APP_TOKEN, SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET, and GEMINI_API_KEY.
2. In your Slack App configuration, change from "Socket Mode" to "Event Subscriptions".
3. Set the Request URL to your publicly accessible server + "/slack/events" (e.g., using ngrok).
4. Subscribe to the bot events: team_join, user_change, message.im.
5. Add your slash commands under "Slash Commands" pointing to the same Request URL.
6. Enable "Interactivity & Shortcuts" and use the same Request URL.
7. Run with: uvicorn main:api_app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

Event Subscriptions:

    Subscribe to bot events:

        message.im
        team_join
        user_change

OAuth & Permissions:
    Scopes:
        channels:read
        chat:write
        commands
        im:history
        im:write
        users:read

Slash Commands:
    /set-birthday
    /birthday-settings
    /reset-birthday-bot
    /set-birthday
    /test-birthday-ai
    /set-anniversary
    /list-birthdays
    /list-anniversaries
    /setup-anniversary
    /test-anniversary-ai
    /delete
    /help
    /set-game
    /test-game

